      <font face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="2">



      <P><I><B>R.S.</b></i> Page four of <I>View</I> magazine reproduces your



        poem &quot;Flag of Ecstasy,&quot; an homage to Duchamp, superimposed on



        a detail of Man Ray’s &quot;Dust Breeding&quot;, showing the lower part



        of the Large Glass. How did this come about, &quot;Dust Breeding&quot;



        with your poem on it?</P>



      <B></B>



      <P><I><B>C.H.F.</b></i> Well, it’s something that the printer superimposed.</P>



      <B></B>



      <P><I><B>R.S.</b></i> Did you pick it out for your poem or did Parker Tyler 



        who did the typography of your <I>Poets for Painters</I>, published in 



        the same year and also reproducing &quot;Flag of Ecstasy&quot;?</P>



      <B></B>



      <P><I><B>C.H.F.</b></i> I don’t remember ... so much water under the bridge,



        I can’t remember.</P>



      <B></B>



      <P><I><B>R.S.</b></i> It’s a fabulous poem.</P>



      <P><I><B>Thomas Girst:</b></i> Your poem on Duchamp is a great one.</P>



      <B></B>



      <P><I><B>C.H.F.</b></i> You like it?</P>



      <B></B>



      <P><I><B>T.G.</b></i> Yes, I do.</P>



      <B></B>



      <P><I><B>R.S.</b></i> Could you read it for us? Do you read your poetry



        still?</P>



      <B></B> </font>



