      <P><font face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="2">Over a stactometer for 



        the tears of France<br>



        Over unmanageable hermaphrodites</font></P>



      <P><font face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="2">Over the rattlesnake sexlessness of art-lovers<br>



      Over the shithouse enigmas of art-haters</font></P>



      <P><font face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="2">Over the son’s lascivious serum<br>



      Over the sewage of the moon</font></P>



      <P><font face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="2">Over the saints of debauchery<br>



      Over criminals made of gold</font></P>



      <P><font face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="2">Over the princes of delirium<br>



      Over the paupers of peace</font></P>



      <P><font face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="2">Over signs foretelling the end of the world<br>



      Over signs foretelling the beginning of a world</font></P>



      <P><font face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="2">Like one of those tender strips of flesh<br>



      On either side of the vertebral column</font></P>



      <P><font face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="2">Marcel, wave!</font></P>



	  <font face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="2">



      <P><I><B>Penny Arcade: </b></i> Marvelous.</P>



      <B></B> </font> <font face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="2">



      <P><I><B>R.S.</b></i> Great, wonderful, beautiful. Thank you</P>



      <B></B>



      <P><I><B>C.H.F.</b></i> I’m out of practice, I don’t read. People ask me



        to read and I don’t usually read. But you win.</P>



